<li id="cite_note-thn-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-thn_17-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-thn_17-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLatour2000" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/Bruno_Latour" title="Bruno Latour">Latour, Bruno</a> (March 2000). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://spire.sciencespo.fr/hdl:/2441/5l6uh8ogmqildh09h61ih1289/resources/2000-latour-when-things-strike-back-vauteur.pdf">"When things strike back: a possible contribution of 'science studies' to the social sciences"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/British_Journal_of_Sociology" class="mw-redirect" title="British Journal of Sociology">British Journal of Sociology</a></i>. <b>51</b> (1): 107–123. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1111%2Fj.1468-4446.2000.00107.x">10.1111/j.1468-4446.2000.00107.x</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=British+Journal+of+Sociology&amp;rft.atitle=When+things+strike+back%3A+a+possible+contribution+of+%27science+studies%27+to+the+social+sciences&amp;rft.volume=51&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=107-123&amp;rft.date=2000-03&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1468-4446.2000.00107.x&amp;rft.aulast=Latour&amp;rft.aufirst=Bruno&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fspire.sciencespo.fr%2Fhdl%3A%2F2441%2F5l6uh8ogmqildh09h61ih1289%2Fresources%2F2000-latour-when-things-strike-back-vauteur.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AScience+studies" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In premodern times (and various languages) the term both meant an object and <a href="/wiki/Thing_(assembly)" title="Thing (assembly)">an assembly</a></span>
</li>
